## 2. Drei Components for the Hero

### Float -- Gentle Floating Animation

```tsx
import { Float } from "@react-three/drei";

// Wrap any mesh to add ambient floating motion
<Float
  speed={1.5}             // animation speed multiplier
  rotationIntensity={0.3} // subtle XYZ rotation
  floatIntensity={0.8}    // up/down displacement
  floatingRange={[-0.1, 0.1]}  // Y-axis range
>
  <mesh>
    <sphereGeometry args={[1, 64, 64]} />
    <meshStandardMaterial color="hotpink" />
  </mesh>
</Float>
```

### MeshTransmissionMaterial -- Glass Spheres

This is the enhanced version of `MeshPhysicalMaterial` from drei. It renders an additional pass of the scene for realistic refraction, so it is more expensive but much more visually striking than CSS gradients.

```tsx
import { MeshTransmissionMaterial, Environment } from "@react-three/drei";

function GlassSphere({ position, color }: { position: [number, number, number]; color: string }) {
  return (
    <Float speed={1.2} rotationIntensity={0.2} floatIntensity={0.6}>
      <mesh position={position}>
        <sphereGeometry args={[0.6, 64, 64]} />
        <MeshTransmissionMaterial
          transmission={1}        // fully transparent
          thickness={0.5}         // refraction depth
          roughness={0.05}        // near-perfect glass
          chromaticAberration={0.03}
          anisotropicBlur={0.1}
          ior={1.5}               // glass-like refraction index
          color={color}
          backside                // render inside surface too
          backsideThickness={0.3}
          resolution={256}        // lower = faster; 256 is a good balance
          samples={8}
        />
      </mesh>
    </Float>
  );
}
```

**TypeScript props for MeshTransmissionMaterial (key ones):**

| Prop | Type | Default | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|---------|
| `transmission` | number | 1 | 0 = opaque, 1 = fully transmissive |
| `thickness` | number | 0 | Refraction depth |
| `roughness` | number | 0 | Blur/frost (0.05-0.15 for soft glass) |
| `chromaticAberration` | number | 0.03 | Rainbow edge dispersion |
| `ior` | number | 1.5 | Index of refraction (glass = 1.5, diamond = 2.42) |
| `distortion` | number | 0 | Noise-based distortion |
| `resolution` | number | undefined | FBO resolution (lower = faster) |
| `samples` | number | 6 | Refraction samples |
| `backside` | boolean | false | Render back surface (better look, 2x cost) |
| `color` | string | -- | Tint colour |

**Performance note:** Each `MeshTransmissionMaterial` requires an extra render pass. For multiple glass spheres, use a **shared FBO buffer**:

```tsx
import { useFBO } from "@react-three/drei";
import { useFrame } from "@react-three/fiber";

function SharedGlassScene() {
  const buffer = useFBO();

  useFrame((state) => {
    state.gl.setRenderTarget(buffer);
    state.gl.render(state.scene, state.camera);
    state.gl.setRenderTarget(null);
  });

  return (
    <>
      <mesh position={[-1, 0, 0]}>
        <sphereGeometry args={[0.5, 64, 64]} />
        <MeshTransmissionMaterial buffer={buffer.texture} transmission={1} thickness={0.3} />
      </mesh>
      <mesh position={[1, 0.5, 0]}>
        <sphereGeometry args={[0.4, 64, 64]} />
        <MeshTransmissionMaterial buffer={buffer.texture} transmission={1} thickness={0.2} />
      </mesh>
    </>
  );
}
```

### Environment -- Realistic Lighting

```tsx
<Environment preset="city" />   // or "studio", "sunset", "dawn", "warehouse", "apartment"
```

Presets load HDR environment maps. For the lightest option, use `preset="studio"` or provide a custom low-res HDRI.

### ContactShadows -- Grounding Objects

```tsx
<ContactShadows
  position={[0, -1.5, 0]}
  opacity={0.25}
  blur={2.5}
  far={4}
  resolution={256}
  color="#1a1a1a"
/>
```

### Stage -- All-in-One Setup

```tsx
import { Stage } from "@react-three/drei";

<Stage adjustCamera intensity={0.5} shadows="contact" environment="city">
  <mesh />
</Stage>
```

Stage combines Environment, ContactShadows, and camera adjustment in one component. Good for quick prototyping.

