### Approach 3: React Three Fiber (Real-Time 3D)

**The idea**: Use `@react-three/fiber` and `@react-three/drei` to render actual 3D paper geometry with real-time lighting and physics.

**Architecture** (from [Olivier Larose's tutorial](https://blog.olivierlarose.com/tutorials/3d-float-effect) and [pmndrs/react-three-next](https://github.com/pmndrs/react-three-next)):

```tsx
'use client';
import { Canvas } from '@react-three/fiber';
import { Float, Environment, ContactShadows } from '@react-three/drei';

function PaperSheet({ position, rotation }: Props) {
  return (
    <Float speed={2} rotationIntensity={0.3} floatIntensity={0.5}>
      <mesh position={position} rotation={rotation} castShadow>
        <planeGeometry args={[2, 2.8, 32, 32]} />
        <meshStandardMaterial
          color="#FDFCFA"
          roughness={0.95}
          metalness={0}
          side={DoubleSide}
          // Vertex displacement for paper bend
        />
      </mesh>
    </Float>
  );
}

function HeroScene() {
  return (
    <Canvas shadows camera={{ position: [0, 0, 8], fov: 35 }}>
      <Environment preset="studio" />
      <ContactShadows position={[0, -2, 0]} opacity={0.3} blur={2} />
      <PaperSheet position={[-1.5, 0.5, 0]} rotation={[0.05, -0.15, -0.2]} />
      <PaperSheet position={[0, 0.8, 0.5]} rotation={[-0.03, 0.08, -0.08]} />
      <PaperSheet position={[1.2, 0.2, -0.3]} rotation={[0.08, 0.18, 0.1]} />
    </Canvas>
  );
}
```

For paper bending, you would apply vertex displacement in a custom shader or use `@react-three/cannon` for soft-body physics (from the [Codrops cloth tutorial](https://tympanus.net/codrops/2020/02/11/how-to-create-a-physics-based-3d-cloth-with-cannon-js-and-three-js/)). The cloth simulation uses Verlet integration with distance constraints between neighboring vertices, mass per particle, and `linearDamping: 0.8` to prevent infinite oscillation.

The `ContactShadows` component from drei renders a shadow plane beneath objects that responds to their actual geometry, solving the rectangular-shadow problem entirely.

**Text rendering on papers**: Use `@react-three/drei`'s `Html` component or render text to a Canvas texture, which maps onto the paper mesh UV. The HTML approach is simpler but less performant.

**Evaluation**:
| Criterion | Score |
|-----------|-------|
| Visual quality | 9/10 -- real-time lighting, proper shadows, interactive parallax |
| Performance | 5/10 -- WebGL context, ~150KB+ bundle for R3F + drei, GPU usage on every frame, poor on low-end mobile |
| Implementation complexity | High -- requires 3D expertise, shader knowledge for paper bending, careful lazy-loading to avoid SSR issues |
| Bundle size impact | ~150-250 KB (tree-shaken R3F + drei) |
| Mobile support | Poor to moderate -- many budget Android devices struggle with WebGL |

**Critical concern for Apollo**: Your target audience is Indian medical PG students, likely on mid-range Android devices. WebGL hero sections can cause frame drops and battery drain on these devices.

