### Approach 4: SVG Filter-Based Paper Effects

**The idea**: Use SVG `<filter>` primitives for paper texture, lighting, and shadow -- all declarative, no JS.

**Key SVG filters** (from [Codrops SVG Filters 101](https://tympanus.net/codrops/2019/01/15/svg-filters-101/) and [MDN feGaussianBlur](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Element/feGaussianBlur)):

```html
<svg width="0" height="0">
  <defs>
    <!-- Paper grain texture -->
    <filter id="paperGrain" x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%">
      <feTurbulence type="fractalNoise" baseFrequency="0.9" numOctaves="4"
        result="noise" stitchTiles="stitch" />
      <feDiffuseLighting in="noise" result="lit" surfaceScale="1.5"
        lighting-color="#FDFCFA">
        <feDistantLight azimuth="135" elevation="60" />
      </feDiffuseLighting>
      <feComposite in="lit" in2="SourceGraphic" operator="in" />
    </filter>

    <!-- Soft realistic shadow -->
    <filter id="paperShadow" x="-20%" y="-20%" width="140%" height="140%">
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceAlpha" stdDeviation="8" result="blur" />
      <feOffset in="blur" dx="4" dy="12" result="offsetBlur" />
      <feComponentTransfer in="offsetBlur" result="shadow">
        <feFuncA type="linear" slope="0.2" />
      </feComponentTransfer>
      <feMerge>
        <feMergeNode in="shadow" />
        <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic" />
      </feMerge>
    </filter>
  </defs>
</svg>
```

The `feTurbulence` + `feDiffuseLighting` combination creates a genuinely lit paper surface with micro-relief. The `feDistantLight` with `azimuth="135"` and `elevation="60"` simulates a consistent upper-left light source.

**Evaluation**:
| Criterion | Score |
|-----------|-------|
| Visual quality | 7.5/10 -- excellent texture and lighting, but SVG filters on transformed elements can be finicky |
| Performance | 7/10 -- SVG filters are GPU-accelerated but can cause repaints; Safari historically struggles |
| Implementation complexity | Medium -- SVG filter syntax is verbose but well-documented |
| Bundle size impact | ~1-2 KB inline SVG |
| Mobile support | Good on Chrome/Firefox, inconsistent on iOS Safari |

